    "url" : "doc:\/\/SwiftlyDocs\/documentation\/SwiftlyDocs\/uninstall-toolchains"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Swiftly"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Uninstall Swift toolchains"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "After installing several toolchains the list of the available toolchains may become unwieldy, and each toolchain can occupy substantial storage space.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This guide covers how to uninstall no longer needed toolchains that were installed with swiftly.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you have a released version that you want to uninstall then give the exact three digit version (major, minor and patch):",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly uninstall 5.6.1"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When you’re done working with every patch of a minor Swift release you can remove them all by omitting the patch version.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly uninstall 5.6"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Snapshots can be removed individually using the version (or main) and the date.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly uninstall main-snapshot-2022-08-30",
            "$ swiftly uninstall 5.7-snapshot-2022-08-30"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It can be time consuming to remove all of the snapshots that you have installed. You can remove all of the main or version snapshots with one command.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly uninstall main-snapshot",
            "$ swiftly uninstall 5.7-snapshot"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You can see the installed toolchains that remain with the list subcommand:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftly list",
            "",
            "Installed release toolchains",
            "----------------------------",
            "Swift 5.10.1 (in use)",
            "",
            "Installed snapshot toolchains",
            "-----------------------------"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Here you have seen how you can uninstall toolchains in different ways using swiftly to help manage your development environment.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
